tive activism and envisioning – a joint investment in futures free of the tyrannies imposed by settler-colonialism.This edited volume assembles collective visions of Indigenous futures, contemplations of the potential of digital technologies, and considerations of Indigenous intimacies, relationalities and manners in which we locate ourselves in an increasingly global, connected world. Together, they present possibilities and the practicalities required to bring them to fruition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aIndigenous peoplesxCivil rights. 0aIndigenous peoplesxEthnic identity. 0aIndigenous peoplesxSocial conditions. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Indigenous Studies.2bisacsh  aDigital technologies.  aFutures.  aGlobal Indigeneity.  aIndigenous identities.  aIndigenous.  aRelationality.  aSocial media.  aSolidarity.  aSovereignties.  aTranslocal.1 aCarlson, Bronwyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarlson, Bronwyn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDay, Madi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDay, Madi, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEnari, Dion, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarrell, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrandy, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaua, Innez, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJensen, Ellen Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJuanena, Coro J.-A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKennedy, Tristan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKennedy, Tr